properties.abstract: To the right you have the Alps (from Mont Blanc to Grand Combin to Wetterhorn), to the left the Mittelland and the Jura (from Hasenmatt above Solothurn to Grand Crêt d’Eau near Geneva), behind is the largest lake in Western Europe (Lake Geneva) and in front the second largest city in the canton of Fribourg (Bulle) and its best-known summit, Le Moléson. If you become tired on Le Moleson, there is an aerial cableway down to Moléson-sur-Gruyères.
properties.subtitle: Walking from top to top
properties.title: Les Paccots – Teysachaux – Le Moléson

sac_photos.title: Teysachaux and Molson, view from Vanil Blanc

segments.description: From Les Rosalys go eastward on the narrow road and take a shortcut to reach ca. 1240 m, then turn left to cross the bridge at 1226 m over the Veveyse de Châtel. Continue on the hiking trail via Vuipey d’en Bas to the "buvette" at Vuipey d’en Haut (1473 m). Now traverse to the SW ridge of Teysachaux and ascend on this ridge. From ca. 1750 m the ridge is interspersed with rocks, and the last stretch before the summit cross (1909 m) is fairly exposed.
segments.title: Les Rosalys – Teysachaux

segments.description: The marked path descends on the steep, grassy and rocky E ridge until ca. 1770 m, then bypasses P. 1788 on the north-west. Continue on the path past a bifurcation to reach a flat passage at 1822 m, called Pointe de Tremetta. From there you hike on Crête de Moléson. P. 1938 is traversed or bypassed on the south side. At the saddle P. 1901 the hiking trail from the south merges. Now directly or past the Restaurant de l‘Observatoire and the summit station of the aerial cableway ascend to a saddle and to the summit of Le Moléson (2002 m).
segments.title: Teysachaux – Le Moléson

segments.description: On a good trail descend the western bowl, then the western ridge and take the bifurcation to the right. Turn around the north foot of Moléson and descend to ca. 1480 m. Re-ascend to the intermediate station of the Moléson aerial cableway (1518 m) or the Plan-Francey mountain restaurant (1529 m).
segments.title: Le Moléson – Plan-Francey

segments.description: Hike northward on a wide trail via Grosses-Clés and Petites-Clés (and Cabane des Clés CAS) to In Maulatrê-d’Avau (1283 m). On paths in pastures and through forests go past a chapel to reach La Savarisa (ca. 1050 m). Now on a concrete, narrow road go to La Grosse-Oubèca, then again on a hiking trail traverse the pastures (climbing over some fences) to a crossroads at P. 868. Continue on the marked route via Prâ-dè-Ma to the southern outskirts of Bulle. Cross the Trême on a foot-bridge and turn right to reach the railway station past the swimming baths.
segments.title: Plan-Francey – Bulle

segments.description: Direct ascent off the «Sentier Panoramique»; http://www.les-paccots.ch.
segments.title: Variant 1: ascent via Petit Mology

segments.description: On the SW side of Moléson branch off to Gros-Plané (1477 m) and hike back to Les Paccots. 1 h less than the descent to Bulle. This variant is also the first leg of «Grande Traversée» from Moléson-sur-Gruyère to Leysin; http://www.id-rando.ch.
segments.title: Variant 2: descent to Les Paccots

segments.description: On the marked hiking trail descend to Tsuatsau Dessus and Gros-Moléson and on to Moléson-sur-Gruyère; T2, P. 1901 – Moléson-sur-Gruyère ca. 1¾ h.
segments.title: Variant 3: descent from Crête de Moléson to Moléson-sur-Gruyère
